extendedInfo.description: Overview:Cisco GIST allows you to measure your mobile connection speeds over cellular or wi-fi (if applicable) networks based on your location and download speed at the time of a test. Whether youâre a diehard Android fanatic or a recent Android inductee, this new application from Cisco will help you quickly understand the âgistâ of what your device is capable of at any given time. This application will also enable you to compare your cellular and wi-fi speeds with other Android users around the world.User Speed Classifications:Web Grade (150Kbps - 449Kbps)Your connection can support Web browsing, email, text messaging and other basic tasks.Music Grade (450Kbps - 749Kbps)Your connection is good enough for audio streaming or downloads and basic web browsing.SD Video Grade (750Kbps â 1149 Kbps)Your connection can support standard definition rich media content.HD Video Grade (1150Kbps and Greater)Your connection is strong enough to support high-definition rich media content.

reviews.title: Cisco really?
reviews.comment: For being a Cisco product it is horribly inaccurate. And I\'m quite familiar with networking but the fact that I will give wrong readings in different networks is very disappointing from Cisco

reviews.title: Script Error
reviews.comment: One day it works fine and the next I get is script error. Great concept to map results and allow others to see how the network performs in different areas. Would be nice if added 3G & 4G icons to differentiate.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: This is Crap
reviews.comment: I get 12.9 meg here and this test says it\'s between 6 and 8 meg. I don\'t expect this front cisco
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Fix runtime error, great app
reviews.comment: Great app to keep the telcos in check. Even though the app has some weird errors when you use it, it embarrasses the U.S. of A.  compared to world average speeds. Highly recommend it. This app benefits Cisco and everyone else in the sense that we get better service, we pay perhaps a little more for it, but the Telco has a better idea where to add more infrastructure
reviews.author: Kenny G. Villacorta S.

reviews.title: Restarts, has wrong date
reviews.comment: Tests say 4/30 on them, but it\'s 5/8. My phone has the date right too, so it\'s your app. Twice I have opened it and had it tell me the app has to restart, no other explanation. Cursory dev work here, can be much better...

reviews.title: Works, but needs a few tweaks for 5 stars....
reviews.comment: Should definitely be resized to allow all data to fit on one screen. Looks like about 80% of the app shows on the screen before being cutoff....  Will not auto rotate. If it did, I could probably see whats been cut off on the right side of my screen.....  No scripting errors/date problems as others have reported.   Other than that, nice app.
